{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "bc22443d-31c5-40aa-9611-d0f5f4b05c1e",
    "name": "Periscope",
    "description": "Periscope API: phone-based auth (register, login, verify-login, logout, me), phone verification, health, and GraphQL (searchUsers). REST: `{ \"status\", \"message\", ... }`. Errors: `{ \"status\", \"error\", \"message\", \"errors\"? }`.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "1288169"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.equal('REGISTERED');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has user and token\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('user');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('token');",
                  "    if (jsonData.token) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set(\"auth_token\", jsonData.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"Test User\",\n    \"username\": \"testuser\",\n    \"phone\": \"+14155552671\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/register",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "register"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Register a new user with phone number. After registration, user receives SMS with verification code. Phone must be E.164 (e.g. +14155552671).\n\n**Expected Response Status**: `REGISTERED`\n\n**Error States**:\n- `VALIDATION_ERROR` (422) - Invalid/missing name, username, phone, or duplicate phone\n- `REGISTRATION_FAILED` (500) - Server error"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login - Send OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.equal('LOGIN_CODE_SENT');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"phone\": \"{{phone}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 1 of login: Send OTP to user's phone. Phone must be E.164.\n\n**Expected Response Status**: `LOGIN_CODE_SENT`\n\n**Error States**:\n- `VALIDATION_ERROR` (422) - Invalid or missing phone\n- `USER_NOT_FOUND` (404) - Phone not registered\n- `LOGIN_CODE_SEND_FAILED` (500) - Failed to send SMS\n- `LOGIN_FAILED` (500) - Server error"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login - Verify OTP",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.equal('LOGGED_IN');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has user and token\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('user');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('token');",
                  "    if (jsonData.token) {",
                  "        pm.environment.set(\"auth_token\", jsonData.token);",
                  "    }",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"phone\": \"{{phone}}\",\n    \"code\": \"{{login_code}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/verify-login",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "verify-login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Step 2 of login: Verify OTP (6 digits). Returns auth token. Store token for Bearer auth.\n\n**Expected Response Status**: `LOGGED_IN`\n\n**Error States**:\n- `VALIDATION_ERROR` (422) - Invalid/missing phone or code (code must be 6 chars)\n- `INVALID_LOGIN_CODE` (422) - Wrong code\n- `EXPIRED_LOGIN_CODE` (422) - Code expired (10 min)\n- `MAX_LOGIN_ATTEMPTS` (422) - Too many attempts (5 max)\n- `USER_NOT_FOUND` (404) - User not found\n- `LOGIN_FAILED` (500) - Server error"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Current User (Me)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.equal('USER_RETRIEVED');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has user field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('user');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/me",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "me"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Get the currently authenticated user. Requires Bearer token.\n\n**Expected Response Status**: `USER_RETRIEVED`\n\n**Error States**:\n- `UNAUTHORIZED` (401) - Missing or invalid token\n- `USER_RETRIEVAL_FAILED` (500) - Server error"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.equal('LOGGED_OUT');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/logout",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "logout"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Logout the current user. Revokes the authentication token.\n\n**Expected Response Status**: `LOGGED_OUT`\n\n**Error States**:\n- `UNAUTHORIZED` (401) - Missing or invalid token\n- `LOGOUT_FAILED` (500) - Server error"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Phone-based passwordless authentication with OTP"
    },
    {
      "name": "Phone Verification",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Verify Phone",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.be.oneOf(['PHONE_VERIFIED', 'PHONE_ALREADY_VERIFIED']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"phone\": \"{{phone}}\",\n    \"code\": \"{{verification_code}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/verify-phone",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "verify-phone"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Verify phone number with 6-digit code sent via SMS. Code expires in 10 minutes. Max 5 attempts.\n\n**Expected Response States**:\n- `PHONE_VERIFIED` - Phone successfully verified\n- `PHONE_ALREADY_VERIFIED` - Phone was already verified\n\n**Error States**:\n- `INVALID_VERIFICATION_CODE` (422) - Invalid or incorrect code\n- `EXPIRED_VERIFICATION_CODE` (422) - Code expired (10 minutes)\n- `MAX_VERIFICATION_ATTEMPTS` (422) - Too many failed attempts (5 max)\n- `USER_NOT_FOUND` (404) - User not found\n- `UNABLE_TO_VERIFY_PHONE` (500) - Server error\n- `PHONE_VERIFICATION_FAILED` (500) - General failure\n\n**Note**: Extract the 6-digit code from the SMS or storage/logs/laravel.log during testing"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Resend Verification SMS",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has status field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.status).to.be.oneOf(['VERIFICATION_SMS_SENT', 'PHONE_ALREADY_VERIFIED']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"Response has message field\", function () {",
                  "    const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData).to.have.property('message');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/resend-verification-sms",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "resend-verification-sms"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Resend phone verification SMS. Requires authentication.\n\n**Expected Response States**:\n- `VERIFICATION_SMS_SENT` - SMS sent successfully\n- `PHONE_ALREADY_VERIFIED` - Phone already verified\n\n**Error States**:\n- `UNAUTHORIZED` (401) - Missing or invalid token\n- `VERIFICATION_SMS_SEND_FAILED` (500) - Failed to send SMS"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Phone verification endpoints"
    },
    {
      "name": "Search",
      "description": "User search via GraphQL only. Requires Bearer token.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Search Users",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test(\"GraphQL data.searchUsers has status, message, data, meta\", function () {",
                  "    var j = pm.response.json();",
                  "    pm.expect(j).to.have.property('data');",
                  "    pm.expect(j.data).to.have.property('searchUsers');",
                  "    var s = j.data.searchUsers;",
                  "    pm.expect(s).to.have.property('status');",
                  "    pm.expect(s).to.have.property('message');",
                  "    pm.expect(s).to.have.property('data');",
                  "    pm.expect(s).to.have.property('meta');",
                  "});"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Accept",
                "value": "application/json",
                "type": "text"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{auth_token}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"query\": \"query SearchUsers($q: String!) { searchUsers(q: $q) { status message data { id name username phoneVerifiedAt } meta { currentPage perPage total lastPage } } }\",\n  \"variables\": { \"q\": \"{{search_term}}\" }\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/graphql",
              "host": [
                "{{base_url}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "graphql"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Search users via GraphQL (Lighthouse). Requires Bearer token.\n\n**Query:** searchUsers(q: String!)\n**Variables:** { \"q\": \"{{search_term}}\" } (min 2, max 100 chars)\n\n**Success:** data.searchUsers { status, message, data, meta }\n**Errors:** errors[].extensions.code â†’ UNAUTHORIZED | VALIDATION_ERROR | SEARCH_FAILED"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
